'''卡倫·伊莉莎白·韋特豪恩'''（{{lang-en|Karen Elizabeth Wetterhahn}}，{{bd|1948年|10月16日|1997年|6月8日}}），是[[美國|美國]][[達特茅斯學院|達特茅斯學院]]的毒物化學教授，亦是該校第一位化學女教授。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mentalfloss.com/article/501147/retrobituaries-karen-wetterhahn-chemist-whose-poisoning-death-changed-safety|title=Karen Wetterhahn, the Chemist Whose Poisoning Death Changed Safety Standards|format=|date=MAY 31, 2017|publisher=|accessdate=|archive-date=2021-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210111072054/https://www.mentalfloss.com/article/501147/retrobituaries-karen-wetterhahn-chemist-whose-poisoning-death-changed-safety|dead-url=no}}</ref>她是一個出色的化學家，專門研究鉻等重金屬對人體的影響，知名於對有毒重金屬的研究<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1997-sep-14-mn-32049-story.html|format=|date=SEP. 14, 199712 AM|publisher=latimes|title=Scientist’s Death Helped Increase Knowledge of Mercury Poisoning|accessdate=|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112034845/https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-1997-sep-14-mn-32049-story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。她死於由一次意外釀成的汞中毒。<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.acsh.org/news/2016/06/06/two-drops-of-death-dimethylmercury|title= two drops of death dimethylmercury|format= |date= June 6, 2016|publisher= American Council on Science and Health|accessdate= |archive-date= 2020-11-30|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201130052652/https://www.acsh.org/news/2016/06/06/two-drops-of-death-dimethylmercury|dead-url= no}}</ref>

==意外身亡==
1996年8月14日，卡倫·韋特豪恩進行有關[[二甲基汞|二甲基汞]]的實驗，她已做好所有建議的實驗室防護措施，例如完整穿戴乳膠手套、在[[通風櫃|通風櫃]]裡進行實驗<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.nationalgeographic.com/science/health-and-human-body/human-body/poison-toxic-tales/|format= |title= toxic tales|date= May 2005|publisher= national geographic|accessdate= |archive-date= 2020-11-29|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201129034758/https://www.nationalgeographic.com/science/health-and-human-body/human-body/poison-toxic-tales/|dead-url= no}}</ref>，但在用移滴管處理二甲基汞時不小心將一到兩滴的二甲基汞撒到手上<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.medpagetoday.com/publichealthpolicy/generalprofessionalissues/80958|format= |title= tiny organic mercury spill did this to scientist's brain|date= July 11, 2019|publisher= medpagetoday|accessdate= |archive-date= 2020-11-07|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201107233412/https://www.medpagetoday.com/publichealthpolicy/generalprofessionalissues/80958|dead-url= no}}</ref>。雖然卡倫當下便立即清理現場、脫掉受污染的防護衣物並清洗雙手<ref name="nejm">{{cite journal|last1=Nierenberg|first1=David W.|last2=Nordgren|first2=Richard E.|last3=Chang|first3=Morris B.|last4=Siegler|first4=Richard W.|last5=Blayney|first5=Michael B.|last6=Hochberg|first6=Fred|last7=Toribara|first7=Taft Y.|last8=Cernichiari|first8=Elsa|last9=Clarkson|first9=Thomas|title=Delayed Cerebellar Disease and Death after Accidental Exposure to Dimethylmercury|journal=New England Journal of Medicine|volume=338|issue=23|year=1998|pages=1672–1676|doi=10.1056/NEJM199806043382305|pmid=9614258}}</ref>，但當時二甲基汞的極強滲透性尚未被科學界清楚認知。

卡倫在該次實驗事故後不久便開始感到身體不適，隨後被發現從頭髮測試出的汞含量於事故後17天便急剧上升，於第39天到达峰值，之後緩落<ref>{{Cite book|title=Delayed Cerebellar Disease and Death after Accidental Exposure to Dimethylmercury|last=David W.; Nordgren, Richard E.; Chang, Morris B.; Siegler, Richard W.; Blayney, Michael B.; Hochberg, Fred; Toribara, Taft Y.; Cernichiari, Elsa; Clarkson, Thomas |first=Delayed Cerebellar Disease and Death after Accidental Exposure to Dimethylmercury|publisher=|year=1998|isbn=|location=|pages=}}</ref>。卡倫的聽力和視力慢慢出現問題，伴隨腹痛及體重下降；次年一月，開始出現平衡失調和口齒不清等症狀，她於1997年1月28日正式入院，後證實是汞中毒<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140715003519/http://stemed.unm.edu/PDFs/cd/CLASSROOM_LAB_SAFETY/Trembling_Edge_Science.pdf
|format=pdf|date= May 2005|title=classroom lab safety|publisher=  Dartmouth Alumni Magazine|accessdate=}}</ref>。她的身體狀況每況愈下，後來因大腦受損嚴重而變為植物人并失去痛覺<ref>{{cite web|url= https://www.nationalgeographic.com/science/health-and-human-body/human-body/poison-toxic-tales/|format= |date= May 2005|title= toxic tales|publisher= national geographic|accessdate= |archive-date= 2020-11-29|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201129034758/https://www.nationalgeographic.com/science/health-and-human-body/human-body/poison-toxic-tales/|dead-url= no}}</ref>，於接触二甲基汞的十个月之后（1997年6月8日）與世長辭<ref name="nejm">{{cite journal|last1=Nierenberg|first1=David W.|last2=Nordgren|first2=Richard E.|last3=Chang|first3=Morris B.|last4=Siegler|first4=Richard W.|last5=Blayney|first5=Michael B.|last6=Hochberg|first6=Fred|last7=Toribara|first7=Taft Y.|last8=Cernichiari|first8=Elsa|last9=Clarkson|first9=Thomas|title=Delayed Cerebellar Disease and Death after Accidental Exposure to Dimethylmercury|journal=New England Journal of Medicine|volume=338|issue=23|year=1998|pages=1672–1676|doi=10.1056/NEJM199806043382305|pmid=9614258}}</ref>。

後來研究發現，二甲基汞可以穿透一般的乳膠手套，並迅速被皮膚吸收<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chm.bris.ac.uk/motm/dimethylmercury/dmmh.htm|format=|date=|publisher=Simon CottonUppingham School, Rutland, UK|accessdate=|title=dimethylmercury|archive-date=2012-04-17|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/66yo4jiX6?url=http://www.chm.bris.ac.uk/motm/dimethylmercury/dmmh.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

==貢獻==
卡倫·韋特豪恩是美國達特茅斯學院的化學教授，對金屬毒性的機理頗爲熟悉，尤其是鉻、汞等金屬。<ref name="#1">{{cite web|url= https://sites.dartmouth.edu/toxmetal/about-us/a-tribute-to-karen-wetterhahn/|format= |date= June 6, 2016|title= a tribute to karen wetterhahn|publisher= The Dartmouth Toxic Metals|accessdate= |archive-date= 2020-10-16|archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20201016225227/https://sites.dartmouth.edu/toxmetal/about-us/a-tribute-to-karen-wetterhahn/|dead-url= no}}</ref>她埋首研究鎳、鉻等金屬如何在人體中代謝，從而導致癌症。<ref name="#1"/>她在大學中出版過多於八十五份研究文獻，教導過許多位學生。<ref name="LATimes">{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1997-06-12/news/mn-2765_1_karen-wetterhahn|title=Karen Wetterhahn; Dartmouth Scientist|date=June 12, 1997|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|access-date=July 11, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714235213/http://articles.latimes.com/1997-06-12/news/mn-2765_1_karen-wetterhahn|archive-date=2014-07-14|dead-url=no}}</ref>她在大學作爲一個統領、綜合的角色，旨在增加修讀科學的女性。<ref>{{cite web
